The national leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Bola Tinubu, has once again stated that his trip to the United Kingdom was to make further consultations with Nigerians and other stakeholders in the diaspora over his 2023 presidential ambition. Recall that it was alleged that the Former Governor of Lagos State travelled to the United Kingdom for medical reasons. However, in a statement posted on his social media accounts on Monday, “Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu promised to continue consultations in line with his intention to seek the office of The President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria.” Uzor Kalu To Other Presidential  Aspirants: No Threat, Meet Me… 2023: Osinbajo Campaign Group Launched In Ondo According to his media team, Tinubu’s medical trip was done last year when he had a surgery on his right knee and “rigorous post-surgery physiotherapy”.